@startuml seq-offline-download
title Offline Download Flow

actor Parent
participant "Next.js PWA" as App
participant "ServiceWorker" as SW
participant "MediaController" as API
participant "OfflineService" as Offline
participant "MinIO / CDN" as Storage

Parent -> App: Enable offline for content
App -> API: GET /media/{contentId}/download-manifest

API -> Offline: generateManifest(contentId)
Offline -> Offline: Resolve best quality\nfor device constraints
Offline --> API: DownloadManifest\n{segments[], thumbnailUrl, totalSize}
API --> App: {manifest, estimatedSize}

App -> App: Confirm download\n(show size to parent)
App -> SW: cache(manifest.segments[])

loop For each HLS segment
  SW -> Storage: GET segment file
  Storage --> SW: segment data
  SW -> SW: Cache.put(segment)
end

SW -> Storage: GET thumbnail
SW -> SW: Cache.put(thumbnail)
SW --> App: Download complete

note over App, SW
  Content now available offline.
  Service worker intercepts fetch
  requests and serves from cache.
end note

@enduml
